Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defendant Erin C Brookins in court with attorney Alejandro A. Lockwood.  Defendant Erin C Brookins in custody.  Thomas L. Potter appeared for Denis Stingl for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  4 YEARS with 17 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence and consecutive to Waukesha County case 13CF1191; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.
Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and the WI Substance Abuse program.  
Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 3 YEARS probation CONCURRENT with Waukesha County case 13CF1191.
  Conditions of Probation/ Extended Supervision if revoked:
- No further violations rising to the level of probable cause
- Cooperate with the Probation Department
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any treatment programs deemed necessary
- No possession of alcohol or illegal drugs;
- Absolute sobriety
- Random urine screens
- No use of prescription medication unless ordered by the doctor and with approval of probation officer
- no contact with Jason M
- Seek and maintain full-time employment
- Provide a DNA sample.
